Five Walter Sisulu University students facing murder charges were granted bail by the Mthatha Magistrate s Court yesterday. The charges of murder, assault with intent to do grievous bodily harm and malicious damage to property related to the death of final-year medical student Lwando Mantshontsho, who was found with multiple stab wounds at the university s Nelson Mandela Drive campus on May 12.To read more get a copy of the Daily dispatch or subscribe to our e-edition online publication.